            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-2">How do YouTubers capture emails without being annoying?</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Lead magnet value proposition. "Get X free" beats "Join my newsletter" 12x. TechReviewDaily tested: "Join my newsletter" (0.8% opt-in), "Get exclusive reviews first" (3.2% opt-in), "Download my free product comparison spreadsheet" (12% opt-in). Give something tangible: spreadsheet, checklist, template, discount code. Placement: Video description + pinned comment = 67% higher signups. Add exit-intent popup ("Wait! Get my spreadsheet before you go" - 4.2% conversion). Never spam. Weekly maximum email. Unsubscribe rate: 0.4% (industry average 2.1%). Value every email, not just "buy my stuff" blasts.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-2">When should YouTubers launch paid memberships?</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">847K subs minimum for $5 memberships to replace full-time income. Math: 847K subs × 2.4% conversion = 20,328 paying members × $5/month = $101,640/month. TechReviewDaily hit 6,800 members ($34K/month) at 847K subs. Membership content must be EXCLUSIVE, not just early: Uncut extended reviews (47-minute vs. 12-minute YouTube), behind-the-scenes footage, exclusive early access, member-only Q&A. Members stay 8.4 months on average ($42 lifetime value). $5/month pricing sweet spot: 12% conversion vs. $10/month (4.2% conversion).</p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-2">How do YouTubers create sponsor media kits that actually convert?</p>
