            </div>

            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-2">Should YouTubers sell merch on their own site or use Amazon Merch?</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Own site: 68% margin, inventory risk, fulfillment headache. Amazon Merch: 35% margin, no inventory, no fulfillment. TechReviewDaily switched: $4K → $18K/month (4.5x increase). Why? Higher margins, more product options, better branding. Hybrid approach works best: Start with print-on-demand (no inventory, 30% margin), test designs, then stock best-sellers (68% margin). Alternative: Digital products ($7 spreadsheets, $17 Lightroom presets, $27 email templates) = 97% margin, $12K/month revenue, no inventory risk.</p>
            </div>

